headline: What CME Group (CME)'s Record October Volumes and Dividend Declaration Mean For Shareholders
summary: CME Group recently declared a fourth-quarter dividend of US$1.25 per share, payable December 30, 2025 to shareholders of record as of December 12, 2025, and reported a record October average daily volume of 26.3 million contracts, with metals and cryptocurrency trading achieving significant volume growth. Analyst sentiment was reinforced by Deutsche Bank's upgrade of CME Group, referencing confidence in organic growth initiatives and the company's expanding participation in emerging asset...
